{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"23fc77ea-9e88-4796-a81a-ecf303de0041","content":"Exit code **8** means \"no tests discovered\" — it's a new behavior in Microsoft.Testing.Platform that VSTest didn't have. The fix is a single MSBuild property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KL7ufqJhfUx5Rt4bgUFfHz","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-46a4a0fcce9a472dbdb9eca6491e595f/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat zero discovered tests as success (exit code 0 instead of 8) -->\n    <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-46a4a0fcce9a472dbdb9eca6491e595f/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"9803320b-ccde-4e78-b5ad-f5deb502c354","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. Microsoft.Testing.Platform returns exit code 8 when zero tests are discovered. With VSTest, zero tests was treated as success (exit code 0). \n\nThe fix is to set the MSBuild property `<TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>` in the project file. This tells Microsoft.Testing.Platform to return exit code 0 instead of 8 when no tests are found.","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"480A:FBA15:3104ECE:35A2DBD:69FBE3D3"},"id":"748531d8-5d8d-4ed5-b4a6-4ac6eceb962f","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:05.369Z","parentId":"26e50992-ea27-446f-a3f1-d3d66376b495"}
{"type":"tool.execution_start","data":{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KL7ufqJhfUx5Rt4bgUFfHz","toolName":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-46a4a0fcce9a472dbdb9eca6491e595f/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat zero discovered tests as success (exit code 0 instead of 8) -->\n    <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>"}},"id":"20726e26-22cc-4b45-8b50-d7c0d542ac3a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:05.370Z","parentId":"748531d8-5d8d-4ed5-b4a6-4ac6eceb962f"}
